
Overview of noun jolt

The noun jolt has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) jolt, jar, jounce, shock -- (a sudden jarring impact; "the door closed with a jolt"; "all the jars and jolts were smoothed out by the shock absorbers")
2. (1) jerk, jerking, jolt, saccade -- (an abrupt spasmodic movement)

Overview of verb jolt

The verb jolt has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) jolt, jar -- (move or cause to move with a sudden jerky motion)
2. jolt -- (disturb (someone's) composure; "The audience was jolted by the play")
